LONDON. &#8211; Alexis Sanchez carried on his Bournemouth hissy-fit into the Arsenal dressing room leaving his team-mates fearing he will leave.Striker Sanchez threw a tantrum on the pitch after Tuesday night s 3-3 draw, throwing his gloves to the floor and visibly showing his frustration over the Gunners suffering a major blow to their English Premiership soccer title hopes. The Chile international, currently locked in a contract stand-off, was obviously furious with his team-mates and the result, and did not speak to anyone afterwards.One source suggested Sanchez known for his fiery temper was angry at seeing players celebrating their fightback from 3-0 down with 20 minutes to go because he saw even a point at Bournemouth as a bad result if they want to win the title. - The Mirror.